WEBVTT

1
00:00:07.370 --> 00:00:18.580
Interpretability explains a model by finding the circuit behind a behavior, scoring each component by the effect of ablating it in isolation.

2
00:00:18.580 --> 00:00:27.750
But transformer circuits self-repair. Remove a primary head, and a dormant backup silently takes over.

3
00:00:27.750 --> 00:00:39.970
Now the primary looks unimportant, because the model repaired the damage; and the backup looks unimportant too, because it was silent all along.

4
00:00:39.970 --> 00:00:45.350
A first-order score is blind to both sides of this redundancy.

5
00:00:45.350 --> 00:00:49.720
CoAx asks a conditional question instead.

6
00:00:49.720 --> 00:00:57.310
Once the primary set S is removed, how much does each remaining unit's ablation effect grow?

7
00:00:57.310 --> 00:01:09.070
A dormant backup has almost no effect alone, but a large effect once its primary is gone. The score is label free and needs only forward passes.

8
00:01:09.070 --> 00:01:19.300
The pairwise interaction between heads forms a matrix, and the name-movers and their backups light up as a dense off-diagonal block.

9
00:01:19.300 --> 00:01:26.720
That block is the self-repair module, invisible to any score that reads one head at a time.

10
00:01:26.720 --> 00:01:35.770
Intact, the primaries write the answer; ablate them, and the backups wake up and re-route to the output.

11
00:01:35.770 --> 00:01:49.550
On the GPT-2 IOI circuit, CoAx lifts backup recovery from 0.33 to 0.91 ROC-AUC, above every baseline.

12
00:01:49.550 --> 00:02:01.310
Ablating the primary circuit barely changes behavior. Adding the CoAx backups is what removes the capability, matching the documented oracle.

13
00:02:01.310 --> 00:02:13.650
A first-order top-up overshoots into the core heads; and the same order gives repair-aware pruning that wins from 124 million to 7 billion parameters.

14
00:02:13.650 --> 00:02:23.950
As the primaries are ablated, the discovered heads grow in output norm and start writing the answer, while random heads stay flat.

15
00:02:23.950 --> 00:02:33.890
Freezing the backups to their dormant value removes fifty-five percent of the self-repair. Their wake-up causally drives the repair.

16
00:02:33.890 --> 00:02:46.780
The discovery is label-free and generalizes: conditional completion transfers to the induction circuit across eight further models and six architecture families.
